The One Genuine Limitation of Modular Monolith
Be honest about this one thing — don't pretend it doesn't exist:

Independent deployability and independent scaling are not demonstrated at runtime.

In a monolith, if the reporting module has a memory leak, it affects claims. In microservices, they're isolated. This is a real operational advantage of microservices.

How to address this in your POC:

Acknowledge it explicitly in your README.md and solution approach.
Show the extraction path (module → service = change only the adapter wiring).
Show that module boundaries prevent cascading failures at the design level (circuit breaker interface, bulkhead pattern documented).


